  <section id="ai-and-clarity" class="content-section">
    <h2>On AI and Clarity</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The same philosophy applies to how this site was written.</p>
    <div class="origin-story">
      <p>After 28 years of professional technical communication, my position is this: <strong>clarity is the product.</strong> The prose is just the delivery mechanism.</p>
      <p>I write in streams of consciousness. Always have. What comes out is tangled, recursive, full of half-finished thoughts that loop back on themselves. It's accurate. It's complete. It's also exhausting to read.</p>
      <p>For years, the solution was to agonize. Wordsmith the sentence. Spend twenty minutes sounding "professional" &mdash; which usually meant sounding like everyone else: fine, forgettable, friction-filled to produce.</p>
      <p>I'm not doing that anymore.</p>
      <p>Now I brain-dump, hand it to an AI, and review what comes back. The ideas are mine. The AI's job is to make it readable &mdash; to do what a good editor does, which is get out of the way of the meaning.</p>
      <p>This isn't laziness. It's the same philosophy I apply to code.</p>
      <p>Good code is self-documenting. When I inherit a codebase that needs a novel of inline comments to be navigable, that's a smell &mdash; the code is failing to communicate. Professional writing has the same failure mode.</p>
      <p>"AI wrote it" is a mischaracterization. AI <em>clarified</em> it. The thinking, the investigation, the conclusions &mdash; those are mine. What I'm outsourcing is the friction of translating thought into readable prose. That friction was never adding value.</p>
      <p>My prime directive is clarity. I'm not writing wedding vows. If an AI can take my tangled first draft and make it immediately readable &mdash; and I can review it, own it, and stand behind every word &mdash; the communication succeeded.</p>
      <p>The question isn't "did AI touch this."</p>
      <p><strong>The question is: does the reader understand what I meant to say?</strong></p>
      <p class="methodology-note">Much of this site was built with AI assistance &mdash; content, code, and design. The thinking behind it is mine. The clarity is the point. That's <em>Provider of Clarity</em> applied to its own medium.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
